\n<Roar>I want to become a scholar. If I can solve even one of the
10,000 mysteries of this world, then it's my victory!

\n<Roar>Some people say this place isn't suited for studying, but
there must be things that can only be learned here. I'll
show them that one's birth and upbringing have nothing to do
with scholarship!

\n<Roar>In this world, there are four basic elements: fire, water,
wind, and lightning. And with their combinations, there are
six more, making a total of ten different elements when you
include the single attributes.

\n<Roar>It seems like most people's attributes are reflected in
their hair color. You appear to have fire and wind
attributes, but since your hair is red, maybe your fire
attribute is stronger.

\n<Roar>People with brown hair like me often have water and
lightning attributes. I don't know why water and lightning
result in brown though.

\n<Roar>Um, it's not a big deal, but could you please be a little
quieter? I have good ears, so it's disturbing my studies.

\n<Roar>Please keep the noise down a bit. You're wrestling, right?
Mom, you really like martial arts, don't you? Despite
appearances, you're quite the physical type.

\n<Roar>I have the blood of thunder in me, so I want to become
knowledgeable about machines. Do you know the town of
Emberland? They say doors open automatically there, and
machines do the cooking!

\n<Roar>I think it's better to open doors by yourself, but I heard
they even cook, do laundry, and grow vegetables! I'd love to
visit someday.

\n<Roar>Then I'll bring back lots of machines to this town and
enrich everyone's lives! When life is abundant, there will
be no need to fight over things!

\n<Roar>It's difficult for us to keep living here by ourselves. We
need to quickly gain knowledge and strength, and somehow
earn money. We can't let the orphanage fall apart while Mama
is away.

\n<Fair>I'm the oldest one here! That means I'm the most important!
Second only to Lady Radlo! Show some respect!

\n<Fair>Ah, but I read in a book that important people don't say
they're important themselves! I'm not saying I'm important,
but I am the oldest! I'm really not important! It's true!

\n<Fair>Mama bought me a new dress! But you know, I haven't worn it
yet because I don't want to get it dirty! After all, it's my
treasure! Fufun

\n<Fair>Mommy is gone... But since I'm the eldest sister, the eldest
sister... I have to try the hardest!

\n<Fair>When I can't sleep because I'm scared of ghosts, Mama hugs
me tight! Then I get all warm and fuzzy, and before I know
it, it's morning!

\n<Fair>They say it's not magic, but if that's not magic, then why
do I get so blissfully relaxed? It's so gentle and smells
really nice.

\n<Francois>You know, I actually think that Radroma's mom is pretty

\n<Francois>Hey, keep it a secret, alright? Don't you dare tell anyone

\n<Francois>"Madam Radlo sometimes goes out at night. I wonder if she
